ng MSBuild properties in the project file to automatically enable the feature. Adding the property to the `.csproj` file...\n\nActually, I should clarify that `dotnet watch test` is the typical way to get hot reload during development, but since this project uses the Microsoft Testing Platform with `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, I can configure `--hotreload` directly in the project file to make it persistent across all test runs.","outputTokens":1312,"requestId":"480F:286947:5C882F6:646EF36:69FBEEBC"},"id":"bfecf7df-eb80-4a89-ba5b-34e8f31cea6a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:45:56.033Z","parentId":"b4a79f14-52ee-4117-b0f9-db7bb1adf747"}
